This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on February 21, 2020. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authorities under the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2020 to various government officials. It delegates functions and authorities to the Secretary of State, Secretary of the Treasury, Secretary of Defense, Director of National Intelligence, and Secretary of Commerce. The memorandum also states that these delegations apply to any future public laws that have provisions similar to those referenced in the memorandum. Finally, the Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.